    "title": "Technical Audit",
    "description": "Comprehensive SEO analysis and optimization recommendations.",
    "content": "SearchFit's Technical Audit feature provides a comprehensive analysis of your website's technical SEO health, identifying issues that affect both search engine and AI platform visibility.\n\n## Running an Audit\n\n### Quick Audit\n\nFor a fast overview:\n\n1. Go to **Technical Audit** → **Quick Scan**\n2. Enter your domain\n3. Receive results in under 2 minutes\n\nQuick audits check:\n- Critical errors\n- Page speed basics\n- Mobile friendliness\n- Core Web Vitals\n\n### Full Audit\n\nFor comprehensive analysis:\n\n1. Go to **Technical Audit** → **Full Audit**\n2. Configure crawl settings\n3. Set crawl depth and page limits\n4. Start the audit\n\nFull audits include:\n- Complete site crawl\n- All technical SEO factors\n- Detailed recommendations\n- Priority scoring\n\n## Audit Categories\n\n### Crawlability\n\nEnsures search engines and AI can access your content:\n\n- Robots.txt analysis\n- XML sitemap validation\n- Crawl errors and redirects\n- Orphan page detection\n\n### Indexability\n\nChecks that pages can be indexed:\n\n- Meta robots directives\n- Canonical tags\n- Duplicate content\n- Index status\n\n### Performance\n\nMeasures site speed and performance:\n\n- Core Web Vitals (LCP, FID, CLS)\n- Page load times\n- Resource optimization\n- Mobile performance\n\n### On-Page SEO\n\nAnalyzes page-level optimization:\n\n- Title tags and meta descriptions\n- Heading structure (H1-H6)\n- Image optimization\n- Internal linking\n\n### Structured Data\n\nValidates structured markup:\n\n- Schema.org implementation\n- Rich snippet eligibility\n- JSON-LD validation\n- FAQ and HowTo schemas\n\n### Security\n\nChecks security best practices:\n\n- HTTPS implementation\n- Mixed content issues\n- Security headers\n- SSL certificate status\n\n## Issue Prioritization\n\nIssues are categorized by severity:\n\n| Level | Description | Action |\n|-------|-------------|--------|\n| Critical | Blocking issues that prevent indexing | Fix immediately |\n| High | Significant impact on visibility | Fix within a week |\n| Medium | Moderate impact on performance | Fix within a month |\n| Low | Minor improvements | Fix when possible |\n\n## AEO-Specific Checks\n\nSearchFit includes AI visibility-specific audits:\n\n### Entity Clarity\n- Brand entity definition\n- Organization schema\n- About page optimization\n\n### Answer Optimization\n- FAQ implementation\n- Question-based content structure\n- Direct answer formatting\n\n### Citation Readiness\n- Source credibility signals\n- Author information\n- Publication dates\n\n## Comparison Reports\n\nCompare audits over time:\n\n1. Run regular audits\n2. Go to **Technical Audit** → **Compare**\n3. Select two audit dates\n4. View improvements and regressions\n\n## Automated Monitoring\n\nSet up continuous monitoring:\n\n1. Go to **Technical Audit** → **Monitoring**\n2. Enable automated weekly audits\n3. Configure alert thresholds\n4. Receive notifications for new issues\n\n## Exporting Results\n\nExport audit data in multiple formats:\n\n- **PDF Report** - Formatted for stakeholders\n- **CSV Data** - Raw issue data\n- **Task List** - Import to project management tools\n\n## Best Practices\n\n1. **Audit monthly** - Run full audits at least monthly\n2. **Fix critical first** - Prioritize blocking issues\n3. **Track progress** - Compare audits over time\n4. **Verify fixes** - Re-audit after making changes\n5. **Monitor continuously** - Set up automated monitoring",
